EXP 1: DESIGN OF MICROCHANNEL
AIM:
To model a microchannel using COMSOL and analyze the fluid flow characteristics such as velocity and pressure distribution.

SOFTWARE REQUIRED:
1.COMSOL Multiphysics

PROCEDURE:
1.Model Wizard: Select 3D
2. Select Physics →  Fluid Flow → Single-Phase Flow → Laminar Flow
3. Click Add
4. Select Study → Stationary 
5. Click Done

GEOMETRY 1
 Set Length unit = µm
1. BLOCK (MICROCHANNEL) Right-click Geometry → Block
 Width = 50 µm
 Depth = 500 µm
 Height = 20 µm
Click Build All
Click Zoom Extents
2. MATERIALS
 Add Material → Built-in → Water (liquid)
 Apply to geometry
3. LAMINAR FLOW (SPF)
 INLET Right-click Laminar Flow → Inlet
 Select one face of the channel
 Set velocity = 0.01 m/s
OUTLET Right-click Laminar Flow → Outlet
 Select opposite face
 Set pressure = 0 Pa
WALL CONDITION Remaining surfaces → No-slip condition (default)
4. MESH
 Right-click Mesh → Free Tetrahedral
 Click Build Mesh
5. STUDY ->Click Compute

